Introduction

Jang Yeojun is a South Korean trainee under UNCORE.

On August 12, 2021, he was introduced as a contestant on the survival show Wild Idol. He was sadly eliminated in episode 3.

In 2023, he was a contestant on MNET's survival show Boys Planet but was eliminated in episode 5 after ranking 62nd place. During his time on the show, he was signed under Jellyfish Entertainment.

On September 26, 2024, he was announced as a contestant on JTBC's survival show PROJECT7, which began airing in October 2024. He successfully secured a spot in the final lineup, placing 6th, and became a member of the group CLOSE YOUR EYES.
